# Verification & Wave Integration (Non-Negotiable)

## Never simulate completion

Describing what you *would* do is **not** completing a ticket. You must **run tools** and **show evidence**.

### Lane agent — before reporting ticket complete

Run and paste summary in your handoff to Nathan:

```bash
git status
git diff --stat
git diff          # or diff of expected paths only
```

Then **read changed files** with the Read tool — confirm content matches ticket scope.

| Ticket type | Also run (lane agent) | Do NOT run |
|-------------|----------------------|------------|
| Code (ENG/INF/QA) | **`npm test` (full suite)** + lint/typecheck for touched area | `npm run build`, commit, push |
| Docs (DOC) | Confirm new/updated `.md` exists on disk | — |

**Fail closed:** If `git diff` is empty or files missing → ticket is **NOT complete**. Keep working.

### Nathan — before wave commit/push

After **all** wave tickets hand off:

1. `git status` + `git diff` per ticket — reject empty diffs
2. Acceptance criteria check per ticket
3. `npm run lint && npm run typecheck && npm test && npm run build` — **all tests must pass (zero failures)**
4. Firestore touched → `npm run test:rules` — all rules tests must pass

**No commit or push if any test fails.**

**Only Nathan** may `git commit`, `git push`, and run **production `npm run build`**.

If any step fails → return ticket to lane agent with command output. Do not commit.

## Wave workflow

1. **Nathan spools parallel lane agents** — one ticket per agent, different lanes, same wave
2. Lane agents implement → verify diff → hand off to Nathan (no commit/push)
3. **Nathan integrates** — resolve conflicts, full build, mark tickets DONE
4. **Nathan commits + pushes once** per wave: `git commit -m "wave(N): ..."` then `git push origin main`
5. **Auto-advance:** After push succeeds → update `project-status.md` → **immediately spool next wave** in the same session (no user prompt). See `07-wave-auto-advance.mdc`.
6. Push target: `https://github.com/cleanerpal/coded-pixels.git` (`origin`, branch `main`)

## Roles

| Role | May commit/push/build? |
|------|---------------------|
| **Dr. Nathan Cole** (Coordinator) | Yes — after wave verification |
| **Lane agents** (ENG/DOC/INF/QA contributors) | **No** — implement + verify diff only |

Default new chat = **Nathan**. Lane work only when user assigns a specific ticket as contributor.
